2. Venezia RA, Agresta MD, Hanley EM, et al: Nosocomial legionellosis associated with aspiration of nasogastric feedings diluted in tap water. Infect Control Hosp Epidemiol. 1994; 15(8): 529-33; abstract available at http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/7983346.
3. Yu VL: Could aspiration be the major mode of transmission for _Legionella_? Amer J Med 1993; 95(1): 13-5; available at http://legionella.org/publications/transmission/could-aspiration-be-the-major-mode-of-transmission-for-legionella/.
4. Franzin, L, Scolfaro C, Cabodi D, Valera M, Tovo PA: _Legionella pneumophila_ pneumonia in a newborn after water birth: a new mode of transmission. Clin. Infect. Dis. 33: e103-e104; available at http://cid.oxfordjournals.org/content/33/9/e103.long.
5. Nagai T, Sobajima H, Iwasa M, et al: Neonatal sudden death due to _Legionella_ pneumonia associated with water birth in a domestic spa bath. J Clin Microbiol. 2003; 41(5): 2227-9; available at http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC154682.
6. ProMED-mail post Legionellosis - UK: (England) neonatal, underwater birthing 20140708.2594991.
